# BYTEC — Curso de Inteligencia Artificial

## About the Project

This is a static HTML/CSS website for the **BYTEC academy** AI course (6 classes). It uses a space/pixel theme with animated stars, slide-based presentations, and responsive design.

## Structure

```
index.html          — Landing page with 6 class cards
style.css           — Landing page styles
clase-1/            — Clase 1: ¿Qué es la IA?
clase-2/            — Clase 2: Creatividad Aumentada & Prompts
clase-3/            — Clase 3: Diseño Visual con IA
clase-4/ to clase-6 — Pending classes
```

Each class has `index.html` (slides presentation) + `style.css` (self-contained styles).

## Design Rules

- **Theme**: Space + Pixel art. Dark background (#060614), orange accent (#f75001), blue secondary (#04589d).
- **Fonts**: Press Start 2P (badges/numbers), Orbitron (headings), Space Mono (body text). Loaded from Google Fonts.
- **Stars canvas**: Animated twinkling stars background via `<canvas>` in every page.
- **Slides**: Each class is a full-screen slide presentation with navigation (arrows, keyboard, swipe).
- **Keep the style consistent** across all classes — match the existing visual components and CSS patterns.

## Slide Presentation Features

- Navigation: keyboard arrows, click buttons (◂ ▸), and touch swipe.
- Swipe detects horizontal vs vertical to avoid conflict with scrolling.
- A **mobile overlay** appears on first visit (stored in localStorage as `bytec-swipe-hint-seen`) explaining swipe navigation.
- Desktop shows keyboard hint; mobile shows swipe hint — toggled via `.desktop-only` / `.mobile-only` classes.

## Responsive Requirements

- All content must be responsive. Grids collapse from multi-column to single column.
- Breakpoints: 768px (tablet) and 480px (small phone).
- Code blocks use smaller font on mobile (11px). Slide text reduces to 14px.
- Nav logo shrinks on 480px.

## Content Style

- **Language**: Spanish (argentinian informal "vos"). All UI text in Spanish.
- **Code comments and CSS**: In English.
- **Tone**: Accessible, practical, engaging. Not overly academic.
- **Target audience**: General public (not developers or entrepreneurs specifically).
- **Exercises**: Include time badges (⏱ X minutos) and step-by-step instructions.
- **Prompts**: Show in code blocks with `<strong>` tags for labels (ROL, CONTEXTO, etc).

## When Adding a New Class

1. Create `clase-N/index.html` and `clase-N/style.css`.
2. Copy the base CSS from an existing class and add new component styles as needed.
3. Include: stars canvas, nav bar, slides container, keyboard/swipe hints, mobile overlay, and the full JS block.
4. Update `index.html` landing page: change the class card from `locked` to `available`, update href, title, description, and tags.
5. Keep consistent slide numbering in `data-slide` attributes and update the nav progress counter.
